WEBVTT

00:00:00.220 --> 00:00:04.201
All right, here we go.
This show is called KILLAH KUTS.

00:00:04.621 --> 00:00:08.521
The basic theme is: concepts you can't air
on terrestrial TV.

00:00:09.021 --> 00:00:14.922
But even that idea is starting to get a
little worn out, and if you're the kind of viewer who's really into variety shows...

00:00:15.122 --> 00:00:18.022
...you might be thinking, "Yeah, it'll
only go so far."

00:00:18.462 --> 00:00:25.263
I get why you'd feel that way.
But with this one, the production team...

00:00:26.003 --> 00:00:30.743
...to put it plainly, is completely
insane. Honestly...

00:00:31.143 --> 00:00:33.863
...I'm just so glad I'm not one of the
young guys anymore. Yeah.

00:00:34.403 --> 00:00:37.284
I'm really feeling that right now.

00:00:44.304 --> 00:00:50.945
These are the people taking part in
today's segment.

00:00:50.945 --> 00:00:52.725
Please take care of us.
Please take care of us.

00:00:52.845 --> 00:00:55.405
Please take care of us.
Please take care of us.

00:00:55.455 --> 00:00:56.455
Please take care of us.
Please take care of us.

00:00:56.725 --> 00:01:01.326
Two of you have already done KILLAH KUTS
before. Yeah, we have.

00:01:01.346 --> 00:01:03.886
We did.
To put it simply...

00:01:04.146 --> 00:01:10.487
...you go into a cage and fight each other
with stun guns. What?

00:01:10.487 --> 00:01:11.287
What?
What the hell is that?

00:01:11.287 --> 00:01:13.727
That's the kind of variety show this is.
It sure was.

00:01:13.887 --> 00:01:18.107
You start wondering whether laws even
exist anymore. Anyway, today's segment is...

00:01:18.567 --> 00:01:23.308
Anesthesia Dying Message.
Oh.

00:01:23.368 --> 00:01:24.828
That's terrifying.
Don't say it so formally.

00:01:25.368 --> 00:01:29.988
That is a scary title. You know the "dying
message" thing you get in murder mysteries...

00:01:30.068 --> 00:01:34.409
...where the victim, right as they're
dying...

00:01:34.829 --> 00:01:38.109
...writes down whatever clue they can
about the killer.

00:01:38.149 --> 00:01:42.269
Right, right, right. That
fading-consciousness feeling at the moment of death...

00:01:42.729 --> 00:01:46.330
...we can recreate that with anesthesia.

00:01:46.330 --> 00:01:51.820
Apparently someone came up with that
brilliant idea.

00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:54.500
And everyone went, "Nice. Anesthesia."

00:01:55.720 --> 00:02:01.400
So this time, each duo splits into a
victim and a detective and takes on the challenge.

00:02:02.410 --> 00:02:06.470
The victim comes to this hospital for an
exam...

00:02:07.670 --> 00:02:12.970
...then gets caught up in an incident
inside the hospital and is killed.

00:02:14.632 --> 00:02:20.033
The instant they're stabbed, the
anesthesia is injected and they drift off to sleep. Brutal.

00:02:20.053 --> 00:02:24.273
Could you explain that a little more?
That's terrifying.

00:02:24.273 --> 00:02:25.233
Then...

00:02:25.233 --> 00:02:29.374
Later, the detective comes in. Then they
find the note the victim left behind.

00:02:29.374 --> 00:02:32.134
They use that note as a clue to figure out
who the killer is...

00:02:32.534 --> 00:02:35.814
If they nail it, it's a success.
Success.

00:02:36.194 --> 00:02:38.854
Success. Why are they taking this kind of
risk just for "success"?

00:02:39.954 --> 00:02:42.995
I was surprised too. There's no
million-yen prize or anything. Just "success."

00:02:43.075 --> 00:02:45.155
Success.
Success.

00:02:45.495 --> 00:02:46.495
Success.
So it's just for the honor.

00:02:46.495 --> 00:02:50.455
Exactly. Since this isn't broadcast TV, we
might even get to see anesthesia vs. Systema.

00:02:50.755 --> 00:02:54.216
Ah. So that's why you brought in the
Systema guy.

00:02:54.216 --> 00:02:59.496
Maybe the breathing techniques can cancel
out the anesthesia. But anesthesia is supposed to cancel out pain in the first place...

00:02:59.556 --> 00:03:02.656
...and then you'd cancel that out?
I have no idea what that means.

00:03:03.797 --> 00:03:06.797
First up, it's Mograider's turn.

00:03:16.238 --> 00:03:17.658
Hello.
Hello.

00:03:18.278 --> 00:03:19.918
Hello.
Please have a seat and wait.

00:03:19.938 --> 00:03:21.298
Oh, okay. Thank you.

00:03:21.498 --> 00:03:28.498
Hey.

00:03:28.619 --> 00:03:31.619
Hey, did you hear?
About what?

00:03:32.459 --> 00:03:39.360
Apparently Dr. Otawara in internal
medicine is having an affair. What, an affair?

00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:41.420
You know Teshigawara, the woman who was
here with appendicitis?

00:03:41.420 --> 00:03:47.460
They say she saw Dr. Otawara going into a
hotel with a younger woman.

00:03:47.460 --> 00:03:49.461
And apparently she's been spreading it
around. Oh.

00:03:49.461 --> 00:03:53.881
I see.
Those are some pretty important keywords.

00:03:55.141 --> 00:04:00.702
Apparently Dr. Otawara's wife took it so
badly she even attempted suicide.

00:04:01.502 --> 00:04:03.602
What?
That is scary.

00:04:05.222 --> 00:04:06.222
Oh, speak of the devil.

00:04:10.746 --> 00:04:12.766
Call in the next patient.
Yes, right away.

00:04:16.247 --> 00:04:19.967
All right then, Tomoshige from the obesity
clinic. Yes.

00:04:20.927 --> 00:04:23.588
Please come into the exam room.
Why him?

00:04:24.568 --> 00:04:27.768
Why not me?
I was here waiting first.

00:04:27.808 --> 00:04:33.449
I'm sorry, we prioritize patients with
appointments. I'm busier than some fat slob like him.

00:04:34.089 --> 00:04:37.249
I'll kill you.
Damn it.

00:04:37.589 --> 00:04:41.310
You can go ahead of me.
Go ahead. It's okay, really.

00:04:41.530 --> 00:04:44.550
It's fine. The obese patient can come this
way. Please change into the examination gown first.

00:04:45.030 --> 00:04:49.431
I'm getting hung up on the "obese patient"
part. Please come this way.

00:04:49.511 --> 00:04:56.391
Since he just got yelled at directly like
that, it really makes you think he's the one who's going to get stabbed...

00:04:56.811 --> 00:04:58.472
...but there's always the chance he just
gets caught up in it instead.

00:04:58.592 --> 00:05:04.172
Excuse me.
Excuse me.

00:05:04.572 --> 00:05:07.233
Oh, hello.
I'm Dr. Otawara, your attending physician.

00:05:07.233 --> 00:05:11.473
Dr. Otawara, yes. Thank you. All right,
let's begin the exam. Please come this way.

00:05:11.853 --> 00:05:18.054
This way. Okay. Got it. And just as
Tomoshige lay down on the exam table...

00:05:19.814 --> 00:05:22.894
...the real doctors prepared the
anesthesia.

00:05:22.894 --> 00:05:27.795
What they're using this time is the kind
of anesthesia often used in routine medical checkups...

00:05:28.975 --> 00:05:33.456
...which sends you into unconsciousness
about a minute after the injection starts.

00:05:35.716 --> 00:05:41.457
And after the dying-message bit is over,
they really will perform a gastroscopy.

00:05:42.737 --> 00:05:47.857
To be clear, this shoot was done as a side
activity during that actual examination.

00:05:48.857 --> 00:05:53.218
Tomoshige from the obesity clinic, can you
hear Ijuin's voice? Yes, yes.

00:05:53.958 --> 00:05:59.359
Very soon, the killer will come in and
murder you. Yes.

00:06:00.499 --> 00:06:03.799
At that moment, the anesthesia will be
injected...

00:06:04.319 --> 00:06:09.720
...so please hang in there and write down
clues about the culprit on the paper by your hand.

00:06:09.840 --> 00:06:11.660
Understood.
Think you can do it?

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.501
Yes. I'll definitely catch the killer.
Best of luck to you, then.

00:06:18.181 --> 00:06:24.502
But I don't want to die.
This is scary.

00:06:25.402 --> 00:06:28.762
All right, we're ready, so let's begin the
examination. Okay, please.

00:06:32.763 --> 00:06:34.143
Excuse me for a moment.
Oh, okay.

00:06:39.243 --> 00:06:40.804
Dr. Otawara.
Hello?

00:06:40.964 --> 00:06:44.544
Handsome guy. I told you not to take calls
while you're working.

00:06:46.044 --> 00:06:47.764
What? A promise?
Come on.

00:06:49.385 --> 00:06:51.005
Let me make this absolutely clear.

00:06:53.145 --> 00:06:57.245
I'm sorry, but don't you think it's time
we ended this relationship?

00:06:57.466 --> 00:07:02.526
We can't keep this up. Hey, are you even
listening? Hey.

00:07:05.226 --> 00:07:07.267
Were you listening just now?
Stop, stop, stop!

00:07:07.867 --> 00:07:13.487
We can talk this out. We can talk. Okay,
okay, okay - aaagh! Huh? Huh?

00:07:15.728 --> 00:07:18.968
No way...
Why would you do that...?

00:07:19.928 --> 00:07:24.169
Dr. Otawara is dead.
So he wasn't the target?

00:07:26.029 --> 00:07:32.470
You were eavesdropping too, weren't you?
I didn't do anything wrong.

00:07:32.790 --> 00:07:35.690
I didn't do anything wrong. What? I didn't
do anything wrong! Stop, stop! Aaah!

00:08:20.930 --> 00:08:22.990
It's started.
He's starting to lose it.

00:08:24.210 --> 00:08:25.770
Huh, this might work. It might work.

00:08:29.371 --> 00:08:35.811
Whoa, hang in there. I play mahjong, so
I'm actually pretty resistant to sleepiness.

00:08:36.872 --> 00:08:41.512
The fact that he's explaining that already
makes me think he's delirious. Don't say such stupid things.

00:08:43.632 --> 00:08:47.113
Look, his hand has stopped moving.
I'll make you happy.

00:08:49.073 --> 00:08:55.273
Yeah. Still hanging in there, still
hanging in there - but his thinking's already going.

00:09:08.835 --> 00:09:09.835
Did he die?

00:09:20.276 --> 00:09:22.816
Did he die?
Whoa, I'm sorry.

00:09:23.196 --> 00:09:29.917
Ms. Kohiruimaki.
I'm sorry I couldn't return your feelings.

00:09:30.677 --> 00:09:36.937
Man, if he'd stayed conscious this long,
there were things he still could've heard. No good - he's stopped.

00:09:55.739 --> 00:09:59.500
And with that, Tomoshige has officially
died.

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:03.920
He held out better than we expected...

00:10:04.780 --> 00:10:07.800
...and it actually looked like he managed
to write a fair amount.

00:10:08.841 --> 00:10:15.841
In dramas you always see things like "The
killer is K..." and I used to think that wasn't realistic, but now I get it.

00:10:16.671 --> 00:10:23.671
When you're writing "the killer is..." you
still think you're hanging in there, then all of a sudden you realize, "Nope, I'm done," and switch to just scrawling a single letter...

00:10:25.122 --> 00:10:26.122
...that really can happen.

00:10:27.622 --> 00:10:31.563
All right, before we move on to the
solution segment...

00:10:31.603 --> 00:10:36.543
...our sleeping Tomoshige will now undergo
the gastroscopy.

00:10:36.803 --> 00:10:41.724
Again, to be clear, this was all done on
the occasion of an actual gastroscopy...

00:10:42.164 --> 00:10:45.704
...and they figured that since he was
already going under anesthesia, they might as well try something like this too.

00:10:45.804 --> 00:10:47.884
Well, of course. There's no way anyone
would use anesthesia just to mess around...

00:10:47.884 --> 00:10:50.905
Using anesthesia for horseplay or fun
would be unthinkable. Right.

00:10:51.385 --> 00:10:53.205
That part was just an extra, strictly
speaking.

00:10:53.845 --> 00:10:57.565
What a beautiful stomach and duodenum.
Doctor, thank you for your hard work. Sure.

00:10:57.965 --> 00:11:01.266
Doctor, from a professional standpoint,
how is Tomoshige doing right now?

00:11:01.506 --> 00:11:05.866
His esophagus looks clean. We're just now
moving from the esophagus into the stomach.

00:11:06.446 --> 00:11:10.907
He is obese, so there seems to be a bit of
respiratory difficulty, though.

00:11:11.447 --> 00:11:13.887
But you're managing that as you go.
Yes.

00:11:16.878 --> 00:11:23.878
Now then, in the solution segment, Shiba -
who plays the detective - has been waiting in another room and knows nothing about what happened here.

00:11:26.148 --> 00:11:30.049
Can he identify the culprit using only the
note?

00:11:39.249 --> 00:11:41.930
Chief.
What's the situation?

00:11:42.470 --> 00:11:45.910
The victims are Dr. Naotaka Otawara of
this hospital...

00:11:46.470 --> 00:11:49.670
...and Tomoshige Yoshiki, who had come in
for obesity treatment. Two victims in total.

00:11:50.771 --> 00:11:56.211
Both suffered stab wounds from a blade
around 15 centimeters long. I see. Pretty gruesome work.

00:11:56.911 --> 00:12:01.312
There are five suspects currently under
investigation. We have all of them gathered here.

00:12:01.532 --> 00:12:05.032
I see.
Then bring them in one by one.

00:12:05.032 --> 00:12:06.032
Yes, sir.

00:12:11.853 --> 00:12:15.633
The first is Maki Jumonji, 30, a nurse at
this hospital.

00:12:17.213 --> 00:12:19.933
She worked with Dr. Otawara for many
years...

00:12:20.513 --> 00:12:25.654
...and because they were together so
often, some people even suspected they were having an affair.

00:12:25.694 --> 00:12:28.058
Come in.
Second.

00:12:28.298 --> 00:12:32.258
Bring in the second one.
Excuse me.

00:12:33.338 --> 00:12:36.158
The second is... ...Yuko Kohiruimaki, a
new nurse in her second year on the job.

00:12:36.858 --> 00:12:43.059
Yuko Kohiruimaki, 24. Apparently Dr.
Otawara was very harsh in the way he trained her.

00:12:43.699 --> 00:12:47.499
And there was a call record from just
before his death. Third.

00:12:47.639 --> 00:12:53.519
Bring in the third one. Kaoru Teshigawara,
38, hospitalized for appendicitis.

00:12:53.839 --> 00:12:58.860
Apparently she had been spreading rumors
that she'd witnessed Dr. Otawara's affair...

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:03.600
...but there were also rumors that she
herself had feelings for him. Hmm.

00:13:04.990 --> 00:13:05.990
Bring in the fourth one.

00:13:09.280 --> 00:13:12.700
Sho Daigoin, 28, who had come in for a
consultation.

00:13:14.240 --> 00:13:20.121
Just before the incident, he was heard
shouting things like "I'll kill you" inside the hospital... ...and there are witnesses who say he was causing a scene.

00:13:21.271 --> 00:13:22.271
I see.
Bring in the fifth.

00:13:26.221 --> 00:13:30.221
The fifth is Manami Otawara, 43, wife of
the murdered Dr. Otawara.

00:13:31.821 --> 00:13:37.502
Apparently she'd been deeply distressed by
his affair... ...and attempted suicide a month ago.

00:13:37.502 --> 00:13:40.242
Hmm.
Do you have anything yet?

00:13:40.622 --> 00:13:44.622
No, at this stage it's hard to say.

00:13:45.922 --> 00:13:49.462
If only we had some other clue.
Chief.

00:13:50.058 --> 00:13:51.486
Under the bed...
...we found this.

00:13:52.102 --> 00:13:53.782
What is it?
Most likely...

00:13:54.402 --> 00:13:59.763
...it's the note Tomoshige left behind
just before he died. Excellent. If we've got this...

00:14:00.763 --> 00:14:06.023
...we should be much closer to identifying
the killer. Come on.

00:14:06.723 --> 00:14:12.723
We haven't gotten any clues at all. At
least tell us if it was a man or a woman.

00:14:21.324 --> 00:14:25.844
Oh!
Oh!

00:14:28.204 --> 00:14:31.764
The girl at reception.
Huge clue.

00:14:32.524 --> 00:14:35.124
Huge, huge, huge.
First off...

00:14:36.025 --> 00:14:41.305
...at this point, Sho Daigoin is out.
Cute.

00:14:43.225 --> 00:14:50.045
My type. We don't need "cute." We don't
need "my type." He must've thought he still had time.

00:14:52.005 --> 00:14:54.505
The handwriting is awful, but...
...I'm guessing this says "affair."

00:14:56.206 --> 00:14:59.786
There's something tiny written at the end
too. Jumonji.

00:15:02.366 --> 00:15:07.006
That's interesting, but let's ignore it
for now. At least we know the culprit is a woman.

00:15:09.786 --> 00:15:15.007
If he'd managed to get down "black
cardigan," though... "The girl at reception" means...

00:15:15.687 --> 00:15:18.467
...someone who works at the hospital.
So it's either one or two.

00:15:20.007 --> 00:15:23.547
Right, we've narrowed it to two.
But "my type" is the problem.

00:15:25.627 --> 00:15:30.447
That just means Tomoshige's type, right?
You know what Tomoshige's type is?

00:15:31.967 --> 00:15:35.328
Basically... ...if he thinks he has a
shot, that's enough.

00:15:35.328 --> 00:15:41.868
That is rude no matter how you slice it.
Still...

00:15:42.368 --> 00:15:47.748
...if we're talking about his type
looks-wise... ...Jumonji probably fits best.

00:15:48.848 --> 00:15:53.108
Out of these five.
Then, Chief...

00:15:53.848 --> 00:15:57.409
...name the killer.
Understood.

00:15:58.289 --> 00:15:59.289
The killer is...

00:16:05.509 --> 00:16:07.609
Maki Jumonji...
...you.

00:16:12.389 --> 00:16:13.630
I didn't do it.
Huh?

00:16:14.270 --> 00:16:17.910
Absolutely not.
Whoa...

00:16:18.770 --> 00:16:22.630
Dying messages are hard.
Hm.

00:16:28.606 --> 00:16:29.606
I'm the killer.
It's me.

00:16:29.606 --> 00:16:35.447
What?!
You die too!

00:16:35.447 --> 00:16:36.447
Fair enough.

00:16:40.727 --> 00:16:44.488
So if you guess wrong there, you get
killed too. Makes sense.

00:16:45.768 --> 00:16:50.628
I may have deduced it based on my own
type. My apologies.

00:16:51.828 --> 00:16:54.049
Chief.
Chief!

00:16:54.929 --> 00:17:01.069
Ah, both members of Mograider died.
Wow.

00:17:01.549 --> 00:17:04.530
Yeah, both members of Mograider died.
They sure did.

00:17:04.950 --> 00:17:08.010
Man, I was so sure about that one.
So...

00:17:08.850 --> 00:17:11.890
Tomoshige has actually woken up and we're
filming him now, but...

00:17:12.450 --> 00:17:15.911
...we don't really know how much he
understood at the time. Right, exactly.

00:17:16.011 --> 00:17:17.231
So let's ask him.
Tomoshige.

00:17:18.031 --> 00:17:19.431
Yes?
Come on in for a second.

00:17:21.191 --> 00:17:22.491
Welcome back.
Thanks.

00:17:23.672 --> 00:17:27.612
Did I manage to do my dying message
properly? Well...

00:17:27.932 --> 00:17:31.172
You were more than half out of it,
honestly. Do you remember any of it?

00:17:31.892 --> 00:17:34.873
I remember writing, but...
...before I knew it...

00:17:35.833 --> 00:17:39.093
...I was looking up at the sky, kind of.
Not the sky.

00:17:39.193 --> 00:17:42.994
Not the sky - you were asleep by then. Do
you actually remember the killer's face?

00:17:43.114 --> 00:17:45.934
I do, I do.
Wait, then you got it right, didn't you?

00:17:46.394 --> 00:17:47.714
We got it wrong.
You got it wrong?

00:17:48.614 --> 00:17:51.854
What? Then want to watch your dying moment
objectively?

00:17:51.854 --> 00:17:56.735
I want to see it.
Yeah.

00:17:56.995 --> 00:17:58.575
Here it comes, here it comes.
Yeah, I can see his awareness slipping.

00:17:58.575 --> 00:18:01.175
See? At first he's actually writing pretty
properly. Yeah, he is, he is.

00:18:03.856 --> 00:18:08.096
This part - "girl at reception" - is
actually the most important part. It really helps. Yeah.

00:18:09.136 --> 00:18:11.396
He still had some room left at that point.
Yeah, he still seems pretty lucid.

00:18:11.936 --> 00:18:14.197
Since he was watching her that closely, he
should've written "cardigan" too. Come on.

00:18:14.197 --> 00:18:16.317
Ah, right.
If he'd written "cardigan"...

00:18:16.471 --> 00:18:17.543
Yeah, but...
...we wouldn't have gotten it wrong.

00:18:17.617 --> 00:18:21.297
I just thought she was cute.
So I wrote "cute, my type."

00:18:21.417 --> 00:18:25.658
Ghh, hang in there.
He's saying something.

00:18:26.018 --> 00:18:29.618
I play mahjong, so I'm actually pretty
resistant to sleepiness.

00:18:30.618 --> 00:18:35.419
He's saying he's good at staying awake
because he plays mahjong. Because he likes mahjong.

00:18:35.499 --> 00:18:38.719
That's not what a guy who's holding on
sounds like. Really?

00:18:39.679 --> 00:18:44.280
He sounds like somebody escaped from a
circus and got shot.

00:18:46.800 --> 00:18:48.740
Looks like he died.
That was fast.

00:18:49.060 --> 00:18:54.181
Faster than I expected.
He's completely out now.

00:18:55.361 --> 00:18:58.941
Whoa, there's more development after that.
He rallies one more time.

00:18:59.001 --> 00:19:02.602
He really does rally once more.
Oh, so he wasn't dead yet.

00:19:03.502 --> 00:19:06.722
Dr. Otawara.
The part where the ring was thrown...

00:19:06.942 --> 00:19:09.642
...he still looked awake there.
Yeah.

00:19:10.022 --> 00:19:14.023
Wasn't that important? No, by then he was
completely mush - nothing.

00:19:14.223 --> 00:19:16.843
So you have no memory of that part at all
anymore? None.

00:19:16.943 --> 00:19:22.784
His eyes were open, though. If he'd
mentioned the ring there, the ring had a name engraved on it.

00:19:22.924 --> 00:19:26.324
Whoa.
So there were a ton of clues.

00:19:26.704 --> 00:19:30.404
If he'd held out another thirty seconds...
...the dying doctor was even saying the name.

00:19:30.404 --> 00:19:31.585
I see.
Right.

00:19:32.005 --> 00:19:37.365
If he'd really gritted it out and kept
pushing... ...you could've identified the culprit.

00:19:37.845 --> 00:19:41.226
No, listen - you can say all that, but...
...it was literally impossible.

00:19:41.906 --> 00:19:46.266
Seriously, I was trying to hold on because
I'm supposedly pretty good at that kind of thing, so I forced my eyes open, but...

00:19:46.606 --> 00:19:47.606
...I don't remember a thing.

00:19:48.326 --> 00:19:52.847
There's one more shock on top of that.
First, my beloved partner watched all that and still guessed wrong.

00:19:53.587 --> 00:19:56.167
And the other thing is, apparently I might
have a small polyp. What?

00:19:56.267 --> 00:19:59.927
Because we did the stomach exam.
Isn't that how cancer starts?

00:19:59.967 --> 00:20:04.968
No, the doctor is a professional, so he
just said you should get a proper follow-up exam. A polyp.

00:20:05.268 --> 00:20:06.448
A small one.
Yikes.

00:20:06.968 --> 00:20:09.688
The sunlight is... Anyway, apparently they
checked everything properly.

00:20:10.749 --> 00:20:14.269
And with that, next up is Raland's
challenge.

00:20:15.380 --> 00:20:22.380
Hello.

00:20:23.490 --> 00:20:24.490
Hello.

00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:31.690
Hey, hey.
Hey, hey, did you hear that story?

00:20:32.550 --> 00:20:36.410
What story?
About Dr. Kondo's medical malpractice.

00:20:37.711 --> 00:20:42.711
I heard. The bypass surgery on Mr. Kakita,
who was hospitalized with heart disease...

00:20:43.571 --> 00:20:45.611
...that surgery failed, right?
Right.

00:20:46.311 --> 00:20:50.851
And then apparently he pinned that
malpractice on Dr. Tanaka. What?

00:20:51.571 --> 00:20:54.672
So that's why Dr. Tanaka got transferred
away? Exactly.

00:20:55.012 --> 00:21:01.212
And I heard Mr. Kakita's son, after
hearing that, said he's going to sue the hospital.

00:21:01.432 --> 00:21:06.012
This hospital is completely messed up.
Wow, that's complicated.

00:21:08.052 --> 00:21:11.313
Hey, kid.
This hospital is no good.

00:21:12.173 --> 00:21:14.993
You should get out while you can.
What are you talking about?

00:21:15.713 --> 00:21:18.293
I almost got killed here once.
See?

00:21:19.133 --> 00:21:20.133
Run while you still can.
Mr. Ichikawa.

00:21:20.533 --> 00:21:26.634
Mr. Ichikawa, please don't bother the
younger patients. I'm just telling the truth, damn it.

00:21:26.714 --> 00:21:30.934
It was just an injection, wasn't it?
Please stop.

00:21:31.214 --> 00:21:34.714
What's all this noise?
Dr. Kondo, sorry.

00:21:35.394 --> 00:21:39.314
There are other patients here, so please
keep it down. Yes, sorry.

00:21:39.754 --> 00:21:41.475
Please do.
Sorry.

00:21:41.475 --> 00:21:42.475
My apologies.

00:21:48.195 --> 00:21:49.495
Big words from a murderer.

00:21:54.335 --> 00:21:56.155
This one's complicated.

00:21:57.536 --> 00:22:04.056
Next, Nishida, here for hemorrhoid
treatment, please come to the exam room.

00:22:04.156 --> 00:22:07.456
Hemorrhoids... ah, right, sorry.
This way, please.

00:22:07.456 --> 00:22:12.136
Okay. Nice, he's even acting out the
hemorrhoids. Very professional.

00:22:13.907 --> 00:22:20.907
A ton of names just got dumped on us at
once, but what makes this one harder is not just the number of people - it's also that they all have really ordinary names, like Kondo...

00:22:23.197 --> 00:22:25.437
...there's nothing to really latch onto
and remember them by.

00:22:27.677 --> 00:22:29.537
Excuse me.
Oh, hello.

00:22:29.738 --> 00:22:32.118
Hello. I'm Dr. Iida, your attending
physician. Nice to meet you.

00:22:32.118 --> 00:22:36.078
Nice to meet you, Dr. Iida. We'll begin
treatment now, so please lie down over here.

00:22:36.218 --> 00:22:42.218
Okay, understood. And just like before,
the anesthesia was prepared.

00:22:42.498 --> 00:22:46.079
We're ready, so let's begin the
examination. Okay, please.

00:22:48.199 --> 00:22:50.679
Doctor, it's an emergency. Doctor, it's an
emergency. Mr. Yokoyama in Building B took a turn for the worse.

00:22:51.439 --> 00:22:53.439
Understood.
Nishida, please wait here a moment.

00:22:53.439 --> 00:22:54.796
Okay.
Please wait here.

00:22:57.039 --> 00:22:58.659
What are you about to do?
Hey!

00:22:58.739 --> 00:23:00.879
Hey, stop!
Hey, stop, stop!

00:23:01.179 --> 00:23:06.260
I'm going to be killed.
Dr. Kondo.

00:23:07.640 --> 00:23:09.500
Dead...
D-Dead.

00:23:10.020 --> 00:23:11.100
I'm finished.

00:23:12.500 --> 00:23:19.161
If that's how it is, I'll kill everyone in
this hospital.

00:23:20.581 --> 00:23:21.581
Die.
Die.

00:23:21.581 --> 00:23:23.661
Scary, scary, scary.
Die!

00:23:24.181 --> 00:23:29.161
There's another one here too.
Die!

00:23:30.561 --> 00:23:33.121
Who?
The one in black clothes.

00:23:33.621 --> 00:23:35.842
Got it.
I got it, I got it.

00:23:37.322 --> 00:23:40.682
The one in black clothes - that's the
killer. Uh, and who else?

00:23:42.062 --> 00:23:46.242
Kondo...
This is bad, bad, bad, bad.

00:23:46.562 --> 00:23:49.822
Ah, this is bad, bad, bad, bad.
He's losing consciousness.

00:23:50.643 --> 00:23:56.783
He blamed the medical malpractice on
Tanaka.

00:23:58.023 --> 00:24:01.803
Who are you, who are you?
I won't forgive what you did to my mother.

00:24:03.503 --> 00:24:09.144
Who are you? Who are you?

00:24:09.144 --> 00:24:10.924
Tanaka?

00:24:13.224 --> 00:24:19.284
Because of you, my mother... He's only got
about a third of his brain working now.

00:24:20.124 --> 00:24:26.505
He's slurring badly, and his fingertips
barely have any strength. What do we do? Give us some kind of clue, Kondo.

00:24:27.885 --> 00:24:32.405
Who are you, Tanaka?
He's down to maybe half... no, a third.

00:24:32.405 --> 00:24:35.085
The medical malpractice was...
I'm sorry.

00:24:35.985 --> 00:24:41.666
I'm sorry. About your family, Kakita...

00:24:43.746 --> 00:24:45.406
He pinned the medical malpractice on
Tanaka...

00:24:48.910 --> 00:24:54.630
I can't write at all.
Who are you? What's your name?

00:24:55.550 --> 00:24:57.391
He just said the name.
He did.

00:25:00.111 --> 00:25:06.771
A black outfit is the best thing to wear
when committing murder. Whoa, he's entered delirium mode.

00:25:09.151 --> 00:25:13.712
The thing most likely to get played on the
radio... ...medical malpractice.

00:25:16.132 --> 00:25:19.892
That sounds like a radio catchphrase.
I have no idea what he's saying anymore.

00:25:21.292 --> 00:25:27.633
And now he's back on something
medical-malpractice-related... ...something about an influencer?

00:25:28.613 --> 00:25:31.893
Nobody said anything about an influencer.
No, nobody did.

00:25:43.334 --> 00:25:45.974
He's fallen asleep. Which means he's dead.

00:25:58.135 --> 00:26:05.135
He held out a long time.

00:26:06.165 --> 00:26:07.165
That's my impression, anyway.

00:26:07.775 --> 00:26:09.475
Maybe he wrote quite a bit.

00:26:09.635 --> 00:26:16.036
He spent a long time talking, after all.

00:26:16.736 --> 00:26:17.736
Chief.
What's the situation?

00:26:18.896 --> 00:26:23.496
The victims are Dr. Takashi Kondo of this
hospital... ...and nurse Kyoko Sakai.

00:26:23.936 --> 00:26:27.256
And Koki Nishida, who came in for
hemorrhoid treatment. Three victims in total.

00:26:27.936 --> 00:26:31.437
All of them suffered stab wounds from a
blade about 15 centimeters long. Mm-hm.

00:26:31.757 --> 00:26:34.117
There are currently five suspects under
investigation.

00:26:34.777 --> 00:26:39.477
Each of them has a motive, so we've
brought them all in. I see.

00:26:39.577 --> 00:26:41.217
You've brought them all in.
Yes, right this way.

00:26:41.657 --> 00:26:43.517
Shall we call them in one at a time?
Yes.

00:26:43.817 --> 00:26:44.817
Chief.

00:26:45.318 --> 00:26:48.898
Chief, over here.

00:26:49.458 --> 00:26:56.458
This note.

00:26:57.698 --> 00:27:01.159
We believe it was left behind by
Nishida... ...just before he died.

00:27:01.619 --> 00:27:03.279
We think it's his dying note.
I see.

00:27:04.539 --> 00:27:05.539
Nishida's note.
Ugh.

00:27:09.099 --> 00:27:14.139
Come on. Please don't let this just be bad
handwriting, nothing more.

00:27:16.700 --> 00:27:22.300
Ugh.
Ah.

00:27:24.100 --> 00:27:26.240
The culprit...
...was wearing black.

00:27:28.170 --> 00:27:29.170
If it's black clothes, then first of
all...

00:27:33.141 --> 00:27:36.401
...which one is it?
What do you mean, which one?

00:27:36.401 --> 00:27:40.721
I mean, I think it's a man.
I see.

00:27:41.701 --> 00:27:43.781
Why do you think it's a man?

00:27:45.501 --> 00:27:50.222
If it were a woman, once he figured it out
he'd probably have just scrawled "woman." I see.

00:27:50.602 --> 00:27:55.082
Wow, that's some incredible
reading-between-the-lines. "Kondo..."

00:27:58.202 --> 00:28:03.723
Whoa, what is this? It looks like some
complicated kanji or something.

00:28:07.003 --> 00:28:09.743
This bit at the end...
...what is that?

00:28:12.063 --> 00:28:16.503
Ah, maybe this was his limit.
You can really see how hard he fought.

00:28:17.423 --> 00:28:23.684
Ah, you're good to pick that up. That's
why you're Ikazu. What is this final part with all the dots all over it?

00:28:24.424 --> 00:28:28.724
A mole?
Tanaka's wife.

00:28:29.304 --> 00:28:30.984
Right.
She has a mole by her mouth.

00:28:31.104 --> 00:28:35.425
You're right. But if we're going there,
this diagonal slash...

00:28:36.265 --> 00:28:40.465
...could also mean a scar on the face,
couldn't it? True.

00:28:41.465 --> 00:28:44.645
Whoa.
What's with the face scar?

00:28:46.325 --> 00:28:51.746
He could've just written "scar on the
face." You're getting really close now. Really close.

00:28:53.406 --> 00:28:56.406
Chief.
It's about time you named the culprit.

00:28:59.202 --> 00:29:02.922
No wonder he'd be furious.
After being scarred like that.

00:29:04.612 --> 00:29:05.612
The culprit is...

00:29:11.623 --> 00:29:15.383
Yoshiharu Tanaka.
It's you.

00:29:19.063 --> 00:29:20.063
It wasn't me.

00:29:23.344 --> 00:29:24.344
Huh?
Hm?

00:29:24.344 --> 00:29:25.344
Hm?

00:29:28.204 --> 00:29:31.504
The police are idiots too, huh?
What?

00:29:32.604 --> 00:29:35.525
You die too!
Whoa!

00:29:35.525 --> 00:29:36.525
Damn it...

00:29:39.965 --> 00:29:44.705
That bastard deserved to die anyway...
Man, we just can't get it right.

00:29:45.205 --> 00:29:50.946
Still, I think we got pretty close.
Whoa, but that was intense.

00:29:51.106 --> 00:29:53.026
You got really close.
Did we?

00:29:53.106 --> 00:29:55.726
You read that really well.
Nishida.

00:29:56.586 --> 00:29:59.386
Yes?
Ah, we got it right. We got it right.

00:30:00.256 --> 00:30:01.256
What?
Come here, come here.

00:30:01.447 --> 00:30:02.747
Okay.
You were right.

00:30:03.107 --> 00:30:04.767
Amazing. That was the thing we were most
worried about.

00:30:05.687 --> 00:30:07.747
Yeah, yeah.
We narrowed it down to two in the end.

00:30:07.967 --> 00:30:09.707
What?
You got it that far?

00:30:10.067 --> 00:30:13.567
Yeah, that "black clothes" clue was
seriously... ...the biggest relief at the start.

00:30:13.987 --> 00:30:15.408
Yeah.
I actually remember...

00:30:15.768 --> 00:30:16.808
Yeah.
...what happened.

00:30:16.888 --> 00:30:20.788
Yeah. I wrote down "black clothes" and the
killer's features, and then...

00:30:21.348 --> 00:30:28.048
..."Kondo..." and then... ...my
consciousness dropped to about a third of normal.

00:30:28.128 --> 00:30:32.749
It just sank. I remember thinking I had to
write down the person's facial features, but then...

00:30:33.449 --> 00:30:37.249
...I remember nothing after that. Ah,
that's why this whole part is unreadable.

00:30:37.849 --> 00:30:40.329
Want to watch it?
Let's watch you die.

00:30:40.508 --> 00:30:43.151
Yeah, I do - I want to see it. Right,
because you don't know what you looked like.

00:30:43.290 --> 00:30:44.870
I don't.
Die!

00:30:45.390 --> 00:30:47.930
Die!
Who?

00:30:49.830 --> 00:30:52.410
The one in black clothes.
He writes it down immediately.

00:30:53.170 --> 00:30:54.870
Right at death's door. The one in black
clothes - that's the killer.

00:30:54.930 --> 00:30:56.770
The killer is...
...the one in black.

00:30:57.651 --> 00:30:59.251
Right, at this point he can't see the scar
yet. Who?

00:30:59.391 --> 00:31:01.871
Who? Kondo...
This is bad, bad, bad, bad...

00:31:02.251 --> 00:31:05.511
Ah, this is bad, bad, bad, bad.
He's fading out.

00:31:06.271 --> 00:31:11.292
Medical malpractice...
Give us some kind of clue, Kondo.

00:31:11.512 --> 00:31:13.872
Wha...
Wh-Who are you? Tanaka?

00:31:14.652 --> 00:31:20.952
Ah, no, no, no... Only about a half... no,
a third of his mind is still working.

00:31:20.952 --> 00:31:24.452
He should be able to see the scar by now.
He sees the scar here - I kind of remember that part.

00:31:26.253 --> 00:31:32.973
A black outfit is best when committing
murder. I don't know anymore. I don't know anymore.

00:31:33.093 --> 00:31:36.993
All in black.
"All-black is best for committing crimes."

00:31:39.454 --> 00:31:42.234
So that's what he was saying.
That's what it looked like.

00:31:42.274 --> 00:31:44.634
There was more, though.
There had to be more.

00:31:44.634 --> 00:31:45.634
From a past life.

00:31:54.475 --> 00:31:57.155
A yawn.
He's like a baby.

00:31:57.255 --> 00:32:00.275
He lost language entirely.
Nothing.

00:32:00.455 --> 00:32:02.575
He died.
A tiny little yawn.

00:32:03.695 --> 00:32:06.896
But wow, the stretch I have no memory of
is really long.

00:32:07.556 --> 00:32:11.576
So you were basically thinking, "Just keep
talking, just keep talking," ...the whole time around here.

00:32:11.636 --> 00:32:13.676
So you were just running on autopilot the
whole time. After that...

00:32:14.436 --> 00:32:19.436
...well, from our point of view he had
died here, so... ...we went ahead and had the stomach exam done.

00:32:19.436 --> 00:32:22.417
And according to the doctor, your stomach
is beautiful. Thank you.

00:32:23.257 --> 00:32:29.637
Thank you very much. Also, while he was
out, there was a bit of... problematic behavior.

00:32:29.897 --> 00:32:37.777
Part of his spirit kind of came back from
hell, so I want you to see this. He was still trying to tell us the culprit.

00:32:37.897 --> 00:32:39.997
He was trying to say, 'The culprit...,'

00:32:41.117 --> 00:32:43.337
but it just came out as gibberish.

00:32:43.997 --> 00:32:46.137
Complete gibberish.

00:32:49.057 --> 00:32:52.577
It was like, 'Eba... ba...'

00:32:53.827 --> 00:32:54.727
'To...'

00:32:55.687 --> 00:32:59.247
'...kyo Hoteison...'

00:32:59.987 --> 00:33:06.147
Like, 'I heard something about who's
getting arrested...'

00:33:07.067 --> 00:33:07.667
'Com...'

00:33:09.237 --> 00:33:10.377
'...a Gossip?'

00:33:10.677 --> 00:33:16.577
'It's Coma Gossip. Coma Gossip came
out...'

00:33:18.017 --> 00:33:19.277
'I didn't do it.'

00:33:23.327 --> 00:33:32.967
They're just young Tokyo comics. That's
not Ariyoshi no Kabe level.

00:33:34.657 --> 00:33:42.117
I figured it was some guy from Ariyoshi no
Kabe who wasn't really on Ariyoshi's level trying to mess with him.

00:33:42.677 --> 00:33:48.377
Like, 'You're not on that level,' and
honestly, my side of the investigation was rough too.

00:33:48.937 --> 00:33:58.917
Reading the clue was hard, and I was
listening as hard as I could too, because I knew Saaya would be mad if there weren't enough clues.

00:33:58.917 --> 00:34:02.937
So the whole time I was thinking, 'I
haven't written anything. Wait, did I write nothing?'

00:34:04.817 --> 00:34:12.677
I was like, 'Maybe I didn't write
anything. Hold on, I want to write just a little more of the dying message.'

00:34:13.697 --> 00:34:15.417
Even though he was still alive.

00:34:16.847 --> 00:34:17.647
What do you mean, 'still'?

00:34:21.547 --> 00:34:23.467
He was talking more than when he was
awake.

00:34:25.087 --> 00:34:28.867
This time, the whole point was to try
resisting the anesthesia...

00:34:29.637 --> 00:34:32.517
...so as you saw, he put up a serious
fight...

00:34:33.177 --> 00:34:37.037
...and his nasal passage was narrow, which
made the camera harder to insert, but...

00:34:38.817 --> 00:34:43.857
...normally, of course, patients can
quietly sleep through the exam.

00:34:45.307 --> 00:34:51.547
So he actually woke up during the exam? If
you watch closely, the anesthesia staff were amazing.

00:34:51.967 --> 00:34:56.827
Whenever he started to toss and turn,
there was someone whose job was to pat his back and...

00:34:57.247 --> 00:35:00.187
...go, 'It's okay, it's okay,' and calm
him back down.

00:35:00.867 --> 00:35:08.467
Because if he moved while the scope was
going in, that'd be dangerous, so if he started going, 'Whoa, Tokyo de-sa...,'

00:35:11.057 --> 00:35:12.137
'...Coma Gossip.'

00:35:12.137 --> 00:35:18.597
Thank you very much. And finally, it's
Minamikawa and Omiokuri Geinin Shinichi's challenge.

00:35:18.657 --> 00:35:20.377
Hello.

00:35:24.558 --> 00:35:25.558
Hello.
Hello.

00:35:25.978 --> 00:35:29.618
Hello.

00:35:34.210 --> 00:35:35.890
A stalker?
Yeah.

00:35:36.490 --> 00:35:43.271
Lately I've been getting silent calls
every single day... ...and I always feel like someone's following me.

00:35:43.371 --> 00:35:45.571
Whoa.
Do you have any idea who it could be?

00:35:45.771 --> 00:35:52.592
I do. My ex is suspicious. And also... you
know Dr. Kakehi from urology? He was super creepy.

00:35:52.592 --> 00:35:56.612
Oh yeah. He keeps sending me gross LINE
messages all the time.

00:35:57.132 --> 00:35:58.712
Ew.
That's awful, right?

00:35:59.212 --> 00:36:00.932
So gross.
Right?

00:36:02.172 --> 00:36:06.433
Alice, what do you mean by awful?
Dr. Shirai.

00:36:07.613 --> 00:36:12.233
Oh, uh... We were just talking about a
drama we watched yesterday being awful.

00:36:12.233 --> 00:36:16.794
I see. Oh, I'm interested in the dramas
you watch, Alice.

00:36:17.774 --> 00:36:19.654
What? What were you watching? What?
Doctor.

00:36:20.554 --> 00:36:23.534
The patient is waiting.
Right, right.

00:36:23.534 --> 00:36:24.494
Yes, yes.
No way.

00:36:24.494 --> 00:36:27.134
No way, no way.
So creepy.

00:36:29.375 --> 00:36:32.355
Hey.
Hey, you - yeah, you.

00:36:32.875 --> 00:36:37.295
Me? Why have you been looking at Alice
with those dirty eyes?

00:36:38.295 --> 00:36:39.335
No, your voice was just so loud...

00:36:39.535 --> 00:36:45.276
I came all the way from Nasushiobara just
to see Alice. Nasu...

00:36:46.016 --> 00:36:47.596
Nasu...
Don't get in my way.

00:36:47.957 --> 00:36:50.315
Don't get cocky. I'm not getting in your
way - I just came here for treatment.

00:36:50.456 --> 00:36:53.337
I'll kill you. No, I only looked because
you were shouting.

00:36:53.697 --> 00:36:55.717
Man, I would not want to get dragged into
this.

00:36:56.837 --> 00:37:00.277
Minamikawa, here for AGA treatment, please
come to the exam room.

00:37:00.497 --> 00:37:06.438
This is nuts... that guy is furious.

00:37:07.758 --> 00:37:11.038
"Stalker," right.
And that doctor in the hospital...

00:37:11.738 --> 00:37:16.298
...definitely has that kind of vibe too.
And that big bearded guy is obviously suspicious too.

00:37:17.039 --> 00:37:18.099
Yeah, he's pretty suspicious.

00:37:19.139 --> 00:37:23.679
And I can't stop wondering about the guy
who's been reading the newspaper the whole time. You can't see his face at all.

00:37:25.379 --> 00:37:27.959
Right this way.
Okay.

00:37:27.999 --> 00:37:31.100
Go ahead.
Excuse me.

00:37:31.100 --> 00:37:32.600
All right, we'll start the treatment
now...

00:37:32.800 --> 00:37:36.360
...but first I'll call the doctor, so
please lie down and wait here.

00:37:36.360 --> 00:37:37.360
Lie down?
Yes.

00:37:38.300 --> 00:37:42.561
And here too, the real doctors prepared
the anesthesia.

00:37:43.581 --> 00:37:46.461
Minamikawa, can you hear my voice?
I can.

00:37:46.761 --> 00:37:48.581
It's Ijuin in the other room.
Yes.

00:37:48.981 --> 00:37:53.942
The killer will be coming in soon, and you
will be murdered.

00:37:54.482 --> 00:37:58.142
They've put anesthetic gel in my nose,
so... Yeah.

00:37:58.982 --> 00:38:01.462
...I can't breathe, and my Systema is
basically sealed off.

00:38:01.962 --> 00:38:05.683
Ah, well, we're not experts on Systema
here. Sorry.

00:38:05.963 --> 00:38:08.903
You'll have to figure that out on your own
somehow. Understood. Sorry.

00:38:11.363 --> 00:38:15.683
Let's see. All right, we're ready, so I'll
go get the doctor.

00:38:16.043 --> 00:38:18.244
Okay.
Please wait right here.

00:38:22.324 --> 00:38:23.544
Aah!
What?

00:38:23.644 --> 00:38:26.724
Why... why me... Die!

00:38:26.764 --> 00:38:30.925
Ando-san, Ando-san.

00:38:30.985 --> 00:38:34.325
Why...? Stop!
Aaah!

00:38:34.325 --> 00:38:36.445
Are you okay?
Are you okay? Are you okay?

00:38:36.465 --> 00:38:40.526
You were flirting with Alice just now.
I wasn't flirting with her...

00:38:40.766 --> 00:38:41.986
I'll kill you. Die!
Die!

00:38:42.866 --> 00:38:45.446
It's kicking in, kicking in.
Wait a second.

00:38:50.378 --> 00:38:56.378
Two people, two people, two people - I...
Uh, an afro, an afro-haired guy, and glasses...

00:38:57.099 --> 00:38:59.899
It's both of them. The guy with glasses -
and a beard, a beard.

00:39:00.539 --> 00:39:04.859
Whoa, something's coming, something's
coming, something's really coming.

00:39:05.779 --> 00:39:09.559
Huh? They're both kind of chubby. Both
kind of chubby.

00:39:09.559 --> 00:39:14.980
Ah, no, ah - both of them, both of them,
both of them are handsome.

00:39:14.980 --> 00:39:19.600
They're both looking at me. They're both
handsome. Kind of Okinawan-looking, kind of Okinawan-looking.

00:39:19.660 --> 00:39:21.660
"Eu gostava dela!"
"I loved her!"

00:39:22.100 --> 00:39:26.420
Kind of Okinawan-looking, kind of
Okinawan-looking, kind of Okinawan-looking.

00:39:26.640 --> 00:39:30.421
Okinawan-looking, Okinawan-looking - ah,
Okinawan-looking.

00:39:31.061 --> 00:39:35.901
Okinawan-looking, yeah. And then, and
then... ...well-built, medium build, medium build.

00:39:35.941 --> 00:39:40.581
Yeah, medium build. Medium build.

00:39:40.681 --> 00:39:43.462
Medium... wow. Wow.

00:39:44.002 --> 00:39:47.682
He's fighting it.
By keeping himself talking.

00:39:48.082 --> 00:39:55.062
Medium build, medium build, definitely
medium build. Medium build. Medium build. Ah...

00:39:56.002 --> 00:40:02.143
He can't get the writing out anymore, can
barely... "medium build." He's saying nothing but "medium build" now.

00:40:02.943 --> 00:40:06.823
White - he's covering all the bases here,
he really is.

00:40:07.243 --> 00:40:13.124
White, white clothes, top and bottom.
That's good. That's good. That's good.

00:40:13.244 --> 00:40:15.164
No way - Muranaka and Carlos? Why would
those two...

00:40:15.354 --> 00:40:22.354
Medium build, medium build, medium build,
medium build. Right, the bathroom.

00:40:22.424 --> 00:40:27.765
Medium build, yeah, medium build. That's
right.

00:40:28.585 --> 00:40:35.245
He is hanging in there, though.
He is. Who, who, who... ah...

00:40:36.565 --> 00:40:42.105
Wh-Who... who... who is in love with who?

00:40:48.666 --> 00:40:55.666
Right - who's in love with who? Ah...

00:41:04.997 --> 00:41:05.997
He's dead.

00:41:15.508 --> 00:41:19.168
And with that, Minamikawa is dead.

00:41:19.888 --> 00:41:25.628
He fought incredibly hard. He showed an
intense refusal to let go of life.

00:41:26.608 --> 00:41:30.549
Whether he actually got enough written
down is another question, but he did write some important things early on.

00:41:35.889 --> 00:41:36.889
Chief.
Yeah.

00:41:38.179 --> 00:41:39.179
What's the situation?

00:41:39.539 --> 00:41:45.740
The victims are Alice Funahashi, a nurse
at this hospital, and Satoshi Minamikawa, who came in for AGA treatment.

00:41:45.800 --> 00:41:51.320
Both were stabbed with a blade roughly 15
centimeters long. I see, I see, I see.

00:41:51.400 --> 00:41:55.041
Apparently Alice Funahashi had been the
target of a stalker lately...

00:41:55.501 --> 00:41:57.941
...and there are currently five suspects
under investigation.

00:41:58.501 --> 00:42:00.021
We've called all of them in.
Five suspects?

00:42:00.401 --> 00:42:03.641
Yes.
Chief.

00:42:06.151 --> 00:42:13.151
We found this under the bed.

00:42:16.622 --> 00:42:20.162
A dying message?
Then this will tell us.

00:42:21.102 --> 00:42:22.102
The culprit.

00:42:32.333 --> 00:42:33.333
Huh?

00:42:38.403 --> 00:42:42.584
Those two?
What was written there?

00:42:42.584 --> 00:42:47.084
Well...
"Afro-haired man."

00:42:53.620 --> 00:42:56.621
"Glasses."
Huh? Wait a second - glasses?

00:42:58.321 --> 00:43:01.101
Oh.
That's huge. This is huge.

00:43:02.401 --> 00:43:07.161
Dark features.
Ugh, I still don't know.

00:43:08.702 --> 00:43:09.702
What's this bit say?

00:43:10.942 --> 00:43:17.482
But the crucial part - he meant to write
"two people," and instead wrote the kanji for two plus an R.

00:43:18.542 --> 00:43:22.703
What about this?
What's that? Huh?

00:43:26.063 --> 00:43:29.943
Two R? Two R?
At this point, yes.

00:43:31.223 --> 00:43:37.924
The suspicious ones are one, three, and
five. Just going by this dying message alone.

00:43:39.464 --> 00:43:45.785
Yeah, but he said kind of chubby, right?
So number one is out. He's not chubby. Then it's three or five.

00:43:47.545 --> 00:43:50.725
Which one is it?
Do we go with the afro or the glasses?

00:43:52.045 --> 00:43:55.205
There's one more twist to it. "Two R, two
R."

00:43:57.146 --> 00:44:01.306
Number one... wait, maybe it's the thing
he most wanted to tell us first. Oh, right.

00:44:02.526 --> 00:44:06.306
Sharp.
Two?

00:44:08.687 --> 00:44:13.367
This looks like an R, doesn't it? But
maybe it's not an R. Yeah.

00:44:13.787 --> 00:44:20.688
Still, I think this has to be it.
Glasses, afro, kind of chubby.

00:44:22.150 --> 00:44:23.670
So you gave up, huh?

00:44:26.610 --> 00:44:31.110
All right then.
The culprit is...

00:44:35.009 --> 00:44:39.489
Shinji Muranaka.
It's you.

00:44:41.029 --> 00:44:45.070
Aah!
Alice!

00:44:45.330 --> 00:44:48.310
Come out!
Come out! I didn't do anything!

00:44:53.890 --> 00:44:59.051
What?!

00:44:59.051 --> 00:45:03.091
What?! No way!
What?!

00:45:06.663 --> 00:45:08.021
Aah!
"Agora tu morre!" / "Now you die!"

00:45:09.012 --> 00:45:11.432
Afro? What do you mean, afro?

00:45:12.632 --> 00:45:15.932
The guy with the afro and glasses - that's
him, right? So why did he stab him?

00:45:17.852 --> 00:45:22.793
So he just did something on his own?
Stick to the script!

00:45:25.213 --> 00:45:30.854
What the hell is he doing? He's useless.
No, that's not it. He made a mistake.

00:45:31.814 --> 00:45:34.754
What do you mean?
You didn't do it, right?

00:45:37.654 --> 00:45:40.654
Don't ignore me.
Afro, you did do it, didn't you?

00:45:42.015 --> 00:45:44.855
Yeah, I did it! Wait, you were the one who
stabbed Minamikawa?

00:45:46.455 --> 00:45:47.715
I stabbed him!
You stabbed him!

00:45:48.215 --> 00:45:52.175
What the hell is wrong with you?
What is this guy doing?

00:45:52.975 --> 00:45:55.416
Wow.
Detective Shinichi.

00:45:56.436 --> 00:45:58.376
What exactly happened here?
What happened?

00:45:59.216 --> 00:46:02.856
This guy just went rogue and did his own
thing. Yes, exactly.

00:46:04.176 --> 00:46:09.857
All of Detective Shinichi's bad habits
came flooding out partway through. They really did?

00:46:10.157 --> 00:46:15.817
He couldn't trust his partner, and he
couldn't keep reasoning things through all the way to the end.

00:46:16.577 --> 00:46:21.578
He even said it himself, didn't he? That
the most important thing would be written first.

00:46:22.058 --> 00:46:23.198
Right.
Exactly.

00:46:23.798 --> 00:46:30.119
It's written while the victim is still
strongly conscious. That's the most important information.

00:46:30.519 --> 00:46:34.699
They wouldn't deliberately step forward
just to draw attention to themselves like that.

00:46:35.409 --> 00:46:42.409
And someone who's innocent wouldn't
suddenly claim to be the killer either. So if there are two very suspicious people, what does that mean?

00:46:45.480 --> 00:46:49.692
The culprit...
There were two of them?

00:46:52.565 --> 00:46:53.779
Look at the first line.
It's two people.

00:46:55.292 --> 00:46:59.453
See?
Where?

00:47:00.593 --> 00:47:06.233
Man, if it's your partner and one other
person, I want you to just write "two people." What is this "two R" thing?

00:47:06.573 --> 00:47:08.573
Listen.
That idiot, seriously.

00:47:08.713 --> 00:47:14.154
No, no, no - you're calling Minamikawa an
idiot while he's getting murdered? Idiot.

00:47:14.394 --> 00:47:18.454
He's seriously unusable.
That's what dying messages are like.

00:47:19.034 --> 00:47:20.034
What's with the half-assed effort?
What were you doing?

00:47:20.114 --> 00:47:22.054
Welcome back.
Wait a second.

00:47:23.435 --> 00:47:27.835
Did you solve it?
Let's hear it from him.

00:47:28.395 --> 00:47:31.875
I entrusted it to you, right? I entrusted
it to you. I worked so hard on it. I entrusted it to you.

00:47:34.055 --> 00:47:37.656
No, impossible.
No, impossible. Seriously impossible.

00:47:37.916 --> 00:47:40.496
That very first part is the important
message. What does it mean?

00:47:40.496 --> 00:47:42.096
This right here - it means two people.
Where?

00:47:43.696 --> 00:47:45.976
It means two people.
Then write "two people."

00:47:46.456 --> 00:47:48.536
Why did you write "two R"?
I did write "two people."

00:47:48.536 --> 00:47:53.197
And for "people" - I think I wrote the
first part of the character. I think I wrote "person"...

00:47:53.497 --> 00:47:57.817
I don't need "I think" - this is
impossible. You get delirious almost instantly.

00:47:58.557 --> 00:48:01.977
First of all, the fact there were two
people is already shocking. We thought there was only one.

00:48:02.637 --> 00:48:07.558
We thought there was only one, so when we
see that we go, "Wait, two?" You can tell from the "two," can't you?

00:48:07.858 --> 00:48:10.878
Then write it as a numeral.
I did write it as a numeral.

00:48:10.878 --> 00:48:14.958
That's not a numeral, that's a Chinese
numeral. Of course it is. I'm the type who uses kanji numerals.

00:48:16.159 --> 00:48:18.879
I can make sense of that. And around here,
he was still alive, right?

00:48:19.279 --> 00:48:23.419
Perfect, perfect. We narrowed it down from
afro, glasses, and chubby.

00:48:23.659 --> 00:48:25.999
Yeah.
Did I really write that little?

00:48:26.419 --> 00:48:30.380
This is totally unusable.
What? You barely wrote anything.

00:48:30.860 --> 00:48:31.860
What is this?
Huh?

00:48:32.420 --> 00:48:34.840
We have the actual footage of your dying
moment. Seriously?

00:48:34.960 --> 00:48:39.080
If you watch it, maybe you'll think, "Ah,
he really did try his best." What do you think?

00:48:39.200 --> 00:48:42.200
Let's watch it.
That guy.

00:48:42.200 --> 00:48:43.200
Aah!
Why?

00:48:43.281 --> 00:48:45.261
Wait a second.
There are two of them, two of them.

00:48:45.601 --> 00:48:48.701
Uh, an afro, an afro-haired guy, and...
I remember this much.

00:48:50.181 --> 00:48:53.941
Glasses... It's both of them - the
glasses, the beard, the beard.

00:48:54.601 --> 00:48:56.542
Whoa. Both of the glasses guys, both of
the bearded guys.

00:48:56.622 --> 00:48:59.082
Something's coming, something's coming,
something's coming. Something big is coming.

00:48:59.862 --> 00:49:01.242
Uh...
Both of them are kind of chubby.

00:49:01.242 --> 00:49:02.562
It's coming now. It is.
Kind of chubby.

00:49:03.122 --> 00:49:04.622
And then, and then, and then...
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

00:49:05.182 --> 00:49:08.522
Medium build, medium build.
Aah!

00:49:09.202 --> 00:49:12.263
Medium build, medium - wow.
Amazing.

00:49:13.163 --> 00:49:15.623
Medium build, yeah.
I'm dying.

00:49:15.643 --> 00:49:17.623
Aah!
You're really fighting for it.

00:49:17.643 --> 00:49:18.843
This is...
By this point already...

00:49:19.143 --> 00:49:22.223
At this point I should've just written,
"12 years in comedy." Ah...

00:49:22.223 --> 00:49:26.324
I've never experienced anything like this.
What kind of segment is this?

00:49:26.324 --> 00:49:30.364
Medium build, medium build, medium build.
He's just repeating the same thing.

00:49:30.584 --> 00:49:32.984
Scary, scary, scary.
I'm scared of myself.

00:49:34.184 --> 00:49:35.484
White.
This is important.

00:49:35.764 --> 00:49:38.545
You knew he came back around.
Muranaka and Carlos.

00:49:38.545 --> 00:49:39.825
Top and bottom.
This is good.

00:49:39.985 --> 00:49:41.465
Why were there two of them?
This is good.

00:49:42.245 --> 00:49:48.385
He was saying something important. He
names two people and says "why two of them," right there.

00:49:48.485 --> 00:49:50.866
I see.
I have no memory of any of this.

00:49:51.946 --> 00:49:55.366
For reference, here are the two people in
question. There are two of them, two of them.

00:49:56.586 --> 00:50:01.966
His consciousness should still have been
clear at this point... ...yet he still made that mysterious writing mistake.

00:50:03.107 --> 00:50:06.267
Ah, and one more thing to tell you.
This is actually good news.

00:50:06.647 --> 00:50:09.207
Yes?
Your stomach was very clean.

00:50:09.307 --> 00:50:11.367
Oh, that's good.
The doctor said so.

00:50:11.447 --> 00:50:13.227
I see, I see.
I see, I see.

00:50:13.227 --> 00:50:15.247
We really are doing the stomach exams
properly. I see, I see.

00:50:15.247 --> 00:50:17.368
You were actually doing the stomach exam?
Oh, good - at least the stomach was fine.

00:50:17.368 --> 00:50:24.208
Thank you very much. And with that, the
Minamikawa-Shinichi pair unfortunately failed to make the arrest.

00:50:24.268 --> 00:50:26.828
Why?!
But we were right!

00:50:26.828 --> 00:50:29.829
Nishizawa-san, this is such a
frustratingly strange feeling, but... ...I want to do it one more time.

00:50:30.169 --> 00:50:36.029
Even after dying that hard.
After dying that hard.

00:50:36.029 --> 00:50:38.429
I feel like I could've done more.
No way.

00:50:38.929 --> 00:50:44.630
I could've done more.
No way.

00:50:44.810 --> 00:50:49.732
I could've done more.
